p: Ethyl 1-((1H-pyrrol-1-yl)methyl)-2-phenylcyclopropane-1-carboxylate (45). Purification using ethyl acetate/petroleum ether (0.8:99.2) afforded the product as a slightly yellow solid in 33% yield. 1H NMR (300 MHz, CDCl 3) δ 7.31 (ddd, J = 18.0, 14.2, 6.7 Hz, 5H), 6.53 (t, J = 1.9 Hz, 2H), 6.06 (t, J = 1.9 Hz, 2H), 4.48 (d, J = 14.9 Hz, 1H), 4.32 − 4.07 (m, 2H), 3.21 (d, J = 14.9 Hz, 1H), 3.00 (t, J = 8.3 Hz, 1H), 1.83 (dd, J = 8.7, 5.4 Hz, 1H), 1.50 (dd, J = 7.3, 5.4 Hz, 1H), 1.29 (t, J = 7.2 Hz, 3H).
